## SECTION 4: UNIFIED PLATFORM ARCHITECTURE

### KEY CONCEPT: Single Blockchain, Multiple Actors

**LIKE COLLEGE PORTAL:**
- Single database (MongoDB)
- Multiple login roles (Student, Teacher, Admin)
- Role-based dashboards
- Same data, different views

**LIKE VERIFYCHIAN:**
- Single blockchain (Ethereum)
- Multiple actor roles (Manufacturer, Distributor, Transporter, Pharmacy)
- Role-based dashboards
- Same immutable ledger, different access permissions

### NO SEPARATE CHAINS PER COMPANY âŒ

Why? Because:
- âŒ Can't track cross-company transfers
- âŒ Counterfeiters could fake their own chain
- âŒ No end-to-end transparency
- âŒ Defeats purpose of blockchain
- âŒ Too expensive (multiple networks)

### YES TO SINGLE SHARED CHAIN âœ…

Benefits:
- âœ… Complete supply chain transparency
- âœ… Immutable from manufacturer to patient
- âœ… Cryptographically secure
- âœ… No single point of control
- âœ… Low cost
- âœ… Real-time verification

### HOW ROLE-BASED ACCESS WORKS:

```
Blockchain (Public, immutable):
â”œâ”€ All transactions recorded
â”œâ”€ Anyone can read any block
â””â”€ Only authorized address can write

Database (Private, role-based):
â”œâ”€ Users collection stores roles
â”œâ”€ JWT tokens identify user
â”œâ”€ API checks permissions
â””â”€ Only allowed actions execute

Dashboard (Role-specific UI):
â”œâ”€ Manufacturer sees "Create Batch"
â”œâ”€ Distributor sees "Accept Batch"
â”œâ”€ Transporter sees "Track Shipment"
â”œâ”€ Pharmacy sees "Accept Delivery"
â””â”€ Public sees "Verify Authenticity" (no login)
```

