## SECTION 8: BLOCKCHAIN BLOCKS EXPLAINED

### Each Transaction Creates an Immutable Block:

```
Block #1: BatchCreated
â”œâ”€ Who: Manufacturer (Cipla Mumbai)
â”œâ”€ What: Created batch B-202412-003
â”œâ”€ When: 2024-12-01 10:00 AM
â”œâ”€ Signature: Cipla's private key (cryptographically signed)
â””â”€ Immutable: Cannot be changed, altered, or deleted

Block #2: BatchTransferred
â”œâ”€ Who: Manufacturer (Cipla)
â”œâ”€ What: Transferred batch to Distributor
â”œâ”€ From: 0x742d35Cc6634C0532925a3b844Bc91e7d8e7f2D5 (Cipla)
â”œâ”€ To: 0xAbc7aF4b6634C0532925a3b844Bc91e7d8e7f2D6 (MotilalOswal)
â””â”€ Status change: CREATED â†’ ASSIGNED_TO_DISTRIBUTOR

Block #3: DistributorAcceptedBatch
â”œâ”€ Who: Distributor (MotilalOswal Pharma)
â”œâ”€ What: Accepted batch from manufacturer
â”œâ”€ QC Details: All seals intact, temp maintained âœ“
â”œâ”€ Warehouse: Warehouse A, Delhi
â””â”€ Status change: ASSIGNED_TO_DISTRIBUTOR â†’ AT_DISTRIBUTOR

[More blocks continue...]

Block #10: PharmacyAcceptedDelivery â­ CRITICAL
â”œâ”€ Who: Pharmacy (City Pharmacy)
â”œâ”€ What: Accepted delivery from distributor
â”œâ”€ Ownership Transfer: Distributor â†’ Pharmacy
â”œâ”€ This is where OWNERSHIP changes on blockchain
â””â”€ Status change: DELIVERY_COMPLETED â†’ AT_PHARMACY
```

